{% comment %}
  Head preloads + small app CSS overrides.
  Previously this snippet also inlined jQuery v3.7.1 (~88KB, render-blocking) and
  ran a MutationObserver that neutered Shopify app scripts (gtag, klaviyo, recaptcha,
  asyncLoad) then re-executed them via eval() on user-interaction or an 8s timer
  (see retired snippets/lazyScript.liquid). That deferral system was removed because
  it was the single biggest render-blocking resource and duplicated the theme's native
  is-land islands architecture. Apps now load as Shopify intends — no intervention.
{% endcomment %}

{% if template contains 'product' %}
  {%- for media in product.media limit:1 -%}
    <link  rel="preload"  href="{{ media | img_url: '500x500' }}"  as="image"  type="image/jpg">
  {%- endfor -%}
{% endif %}
